Here is a clear and concise summary of the key aspects and planned measures for the Energetische Sanierungskonzeption:

Key Information & Current Situation

Location & Type: Reihenhaus in Nürtingen-Roßdorf (built ~1972, 113 m², 3 occupants)

Current Energy Situation:

Heating & Warm Water: Fernwärme (contract until end of 2028, special clause allows early adjustment)

Electricity: Grid-supplied (no PV system yet)

Annual Consumption (2023):

Heating: 9,824 kWh (~3,197 €)

Warm Water: 16.86 m³ (~445 €)

Electricity: 2,671 kWh (~1,024 €)

Main Goals

Transition to renewable and self-sufficient energy

Lower long-term energy costs and protect against price increases

Reduce CO₂ emissions significantly

Improve comfort via smart control, heating flexibility, and summer cooling

Prioritize self-produced energy use (solar PV)

Planned Renovation Measures
1. Building Envelope Improvements

Insulation:

Basement ceiling insulation (target: U < 0.25 W/m²K)

Roof insulation (target: U < 0.20 W/m²K)

Window Replacement:

Modern, triple-glazed windows for reduced heat loss

Facade Insulation:

External insulation (WDVS), if feasible (optional)

Otherwise, internal insulation (Calcium silicate or wood-fiber boards)

2. Energy Production & Storage System

Photovoltaic (PV) System:

~5.8 kWp, south-oriented for high self-use

Battery Storage:

Capacity: 5–10 kWh (cover evening/nighttime electricity demand)

Two Heat Storage Tanks:

Smaller tank for hot water

Larger tank for heating and passive cooling, switchable between summer/winter modes

Hygienic separation via heat exchanger

Water Heat Pump for Hot Water (BW-WP):

Utilizes ambient air (e.g., basement air)

Efficient with PV-generated power

Wood Stove with Water Jacket:

Additional winter heat source, using own garden wood

Connected to storage tanks

Electric Heater in Storage Tank:

PV surplus activated only after battery is full, further optimizing self-use

3. Heating & Smart Control

Underfloor Heating (water-based):

Even distribution, low-temperature operation

Intelligent Control via Home Assistant:

Automation of heating, cooling, and energy use based on occupancy, weather, PV status

Notifications (e.g., reminders for wood stove refill)

4. Summer Cooling Strategy

Nighttime cooling of large tank using heat pump

Passive cooling via underfloor system during hot days

Automatic switching between heating/cooling based on outdoor temperature averages

Estimated Costs

Total renovation cost (without facade insulation): 67,000–90,000 €

With facade insulation: 82,000–115,000 €

Funding Opportunities (2024)

BAFA/BEG subsidies (15–20%) for insulation, heat pump, storage, smart control

KfW Efficiency House funding (credit with repayment bonus)

PV and battery VAT exemption, possible additional local subsidies

Up to 80% subsidy for mandatory energy consultation

Suggested Implementation Order

Insulation (basement, roof, windows)

PV installation and battery storage

Heating & storage system (heat pump, wood stove, underfloor heating)

Smart control (Home Assistant)

Optional facade insulation

Coordination and application of funding programs

Conclusion

The proposed concept combines renovation, renewable energy, smart control, and seasonal flexibility to create a future-proof, sustainable, and cost-efficient home energy solution.

